item.title: About Me
item.description: I am a Research Analyst at Yale's Tobin Center for Economic Policy for Yale's Assistant Professor of Economics John Eric Humphries, and also for Princeton's Assistant Professor of Economics and Public Affairs Christopher Neilson. My interests lie within the intersection of the fields of education, public policy, computer science and technology. Interests beyond academia include anything computers, music, politics (who doesn't), and the natural sciences in general. Prior to this current position I completed a B.
